Wash and dry all produce. Bring a large #pot{} of @salt{} water to a boil. Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}. Pick @mint{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; discard stems. Roughly chop leaves.

Heat a large, empty #pan{} over medium-low heat. Add @pine nuts{1%ounce} and toast, tossing frequently, until lightly browned and fragrant, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from pan and set aside.

Once water is boiling, add @penne pasta{6%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Carefully scoop out and reserve 1/3 cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in same pan over medium heat. Add half the @pancetta{2%ounce} (use the rest as you like) and cook, tossing, until lightly crisped, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add garlic and @peas{4%ounce} and cook, tossing, until fragrant, about ~{1%minute}.

Stir @sour cream{4%tablespoon} into pancetta mixture in pan. Add penne, half the @parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and reserved pasta cooking water. Gently toss over medium heat until a thick, creamy sauce forms, ~{3-4%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide penne mixture between plates. Sprinkle with mint (to taste), pine nuts, and remaining Parmesan.